{"id": 6943, "title": "Ticket #6943: Don't set argv[0] to condor_exe.exe for non file-transfered jobs", "description": "<blockquote>\nToday, even if the main executable of a job wasn't file transferred to the worker node, we set the argv[0] of the to the string \"condor_exec.exe\".  This breaks all kinds of programs in very hard to debug ways.  Eventually, we will allow the admin to opt out of renamed condor_exec.exe for file-transferred executables, but first start with never setting argv[0] for non-file transferred jobs.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Mar-25 13:54</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/297a19f6a79426e4be84c5986d2dfa4ffce52cd9\">[56436]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6943\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6943'); return false;\" title=\"Don't set argv[0] to condor_exe.exe for non file-transfered jobs\">#6943</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Mar-06 14:40</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/3955474b42a6df86bdd1fd5d1c0c0f807ec9e057\">[56288]</a></span>: Don't set argv[0] to condor_exe.exe for non-transferred jobs <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6943\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6943'); return false;\" title=\"Don't set argv[0] to condor_e